Description: I would like to say, I should not have used a white blanket, for a backdrop. In the pic's I can see some white specs. Also this guitar is in like new condition, and has never left the house. Now that I got that out of the way. I have listed this guitar as used, but there is only about 2 hours of play on it. when I got I played it, for about 20 min. Order new strings, so on the guitar right now are Super Slinky RPS 11's on low E, A and D, and 10's on high E, B and G. played it a few more times only in the house, and put it away. What I am trying to get to is this guitar is in very good condition, with little play. So now to the guitar, construction neck-thru, 25.5" scale neck which is a 3Pc maple neck, Rosewood fretboard and a 350 radius. The neck contour is extra thin U, with 24 frets tuners are LTD it has a Floyd Rose tremolo bridge. Neck pickup is an EMG 60, and the bridge pickup is an EMG 81 active pickups. The layout on electronics is Vol/Vol/Tone/3-way switch. The plastic playes on the back of the guitar may look alittle foggy, because the plastic is still on the plates, also the case in the pictures (IS NOT INCLUDED), IT WAS FOR PICTURES ONLY!!!
